msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc24:0.1"
msgid "Theravāda Vinaya"
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc24:0.2"
msgid "Mahāvibhaṅga"
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc24:0.3"
msgid "Pācittiyakaṇḍa"
msgstr "The chapter on confession (_pācittiya_)"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc24:0.4"
msgid "Ovādavagga"
msgstr "Monks’ Confession 24"

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc24:0.5"
msgid "24. Āmisasikkhāpada"
msgstr "The training rule on worldly gain"

#. HTML: </h1></div><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc24:1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Origin story"

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: sc1, pts-vp-pli4.58, pts-cs-bu-pc24.1, pts-vp-en.2.279, ms2V_548
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc24:1.1"
msgid "Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme."
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc24:1.2"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena therā bhikkhū bhikkhuniyo ovadantā lābhino honti cīvarapiṇḍapātasenāsanagilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhārānaṃ."
msgstr "At that time the senior monks who instructed the nuns received robe-cloth, almsfood, dwellings, and medicines."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc24:1.3"
msgid "Chabbaggiyā bhikkhū evaṃ vadanti—"
msgstr "And the monks from the group of six said this about them,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc24:1.4"
msgid "“na bahukatā therā bhikkhū bhikkhuniyo ovadituṃ; āmisahetu therā bhikkhū bhikkhuniyo ovadantī”ti."
msgstr "“The senior monks aren’t instructing the nuns to render a service, but for the sake of worldly gain.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2, ms2V_549
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc24:1.5"
msgid "Ye te bhikkhū appicchā … pe …"
msgstr "The monks of few desires …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc24:1.6"
msgid "te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "complained and criticized them,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc24:1.7"
msgid "“kathañhi nāma chabbaggiyā bhikkhū evaṃ vakkhanti—"
msgstr "“How can the monks from the group of six say that"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc24:1.8"
msgid "‘na bahukatā therā bhikkhū bhikkhuniyo ovadituṃ; āmisahetu therā bhikkhū bhikkhuniyo ovadantī’”ti … pe …"
msgstr "the senior monks aren’t instructing the nuns to render a service, but for the sake of worldly gain?” …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc24:1.9"
msgid "“saccaṃ kira tumhe, bhikkhave, evaṃ vadetha—‘"
msgstr "“Is it true, monks, that you say this?”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc24:1.10"
msgid "na bahukatā therā bhikkhū bhikkhuniyo ovadituṃ; āmisahetu therā bhikkhū bhikkhuniyo ovadantī’”ti?"
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc24:1.11"
msgid "“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc24:1.12"
msgid "Vigarahi buddho bhagavā … pe …"
msgstr "The Buddha rebuked them, “…"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc24:1.13"
msgid "kathañhi nāma tumhe, moghapurisā, evaṃ vakkhatha—"
msgstr "Foolish men, how can you say that"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc24:1.14"
msgid "‘na bahukatā therā bhikkhū bhikkhuniyo ovadituṃ; āmisahetu therā bhikkhū bhikkhuniyo ovadantī’ti."
msgstr "the senior monks aren’t instructing the nuns to render a service, but for the sake of worldly gain?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc24:1.15"
msgid "Netaṃ, moghapurisā, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya … pe …"
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc24:1.16"
msgid "evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc24:1.16a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Final ruling"

#. HTML: </h2><p><span class="rule">
#. VAR: āmisahetu therā bhikkhū → āmisahetu bhikkhū (s1-3)
#. REF: sc3, ms2V_550
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc24:1.17"
msgid "“Yo pana bhikkhu evaṃ vadeyya—‘āmisahetu therā bhikkhū bhikkhuniyo ovandantī’ti, pācittiyan”ti."
msgstr "‘If a monk says that the senior monks are instructing the nuns for the sake of worldly gain, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”"

#. HTML: </span></p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc24:2.1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Definitions"

#. HTML: </h2><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc4, pts-cs-bu-pc24.2.1, ms2V_551
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc24:2.1.1"
msgid "Yo panāti"
msgstr "A:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc24:2.1.2"
msgid "yo yādiso … pe …"
msgstr "whoever …"

#. HTML: </span><span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc24:2.1.3"
msgid "bhikkhūti"
msgstr "Monk:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc24:2.1.4"
msgid "… pe …"
msgstr "… The monk who has been given the full ordination by a complete Order through a procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is unchallengeable and fit to stand—"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc24:2.1.5"
msgid "ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti."
msgstr "this sort of monk is meant in this case."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc5, pts-vp-en.2.280, ms2V_552
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc24:2.1.6"
msgid "Āmisahetūti"
msgstr "For the sake of worldly gain:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc24:2.1.7"
msgid "cīvarahetu piṇḍapātahetu senāsanahetu gilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhārahetu sakkārahetu garukārahetu mānanahetu vandanahetu pūjanahetu."
msgstr "for the sake of robe-cloth, for the sake of almsfood, for the sake of a dwelling, for the sake of medicines, for the sake of honor, for the sake of respect, for the sake of deference, for the sake of veneration, for the sake of worship."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc6, ms2V_553
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc24:2.1.8"
msgid "Evaṃ vadeyyāti"
msgstr "Says:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc24:2.1.9"
msgid "upasampannaṃ saṃghena sammataṃ bhikkhunovādakaṃ avaṇṇaṃ kattukāmo ayasaṃ kattukāmo maṅkukattukāmo evaṃ vadeti—"
msgstr "if, concerning one who is fully ordained and who has been agreed upon by the Order as an instructor of nuns—desiring to disparage him, desiring to give him a bad reputation, desiring to humiliate him—he says,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc24:2.1.10"
msgid "“cīvarahetu piṇḍapātahetu senāsanahetu gilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhārahetu sakkārahetu garukārahetu mānanahetu vandanahetu pūjanahetu ovadatī”ti bhaṇati, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "“He instructs for the sake of robe-cloth/for the sake of almsfood/for the sake of a dwelling/for the sake of medicines/for the sake of honor/for the sake of respect/for the sake of deference/for the sake of veneration/for the sake of worship,” he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. HTML: </span></p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc24:2.2.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Permutations"

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: sc7, pts-cs-bu-pc24.2.2, ms2V_554
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc24:2.2.1"
msgid "Dhammakamme dhammakammasaññī evaṃ vadeti, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "If it is a legitimate procedure, and he perceives it as legitimate, and he says such a thing, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc24:2.2.2"
msgid "Dhammakamme vematiko evaṃ vadeti, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "If it is a legitimate procedure, but he is unsure if it is, and he says such a thing, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc24:2.2.3"
msgid "Dhammakamme adhammakammasaññī evaṃ vadeti, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "If it is a legitimate procedure, but he perceives it as illegitimate, and he says such a thing, he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc8, ms2V_555
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc24:2.2.4"
msgid "Upasampannaṃ saṃghena asammataṃ bhikkhunovādakaṃ avaṇṇaṃ kattukāmo ayasaṃ kattukāmo maṅkukattukāmo evaṃ vadeti—"
msgstr "When someone who is fully ordained is an instructor of nuns, but he has not been agreed upon by the Order as such, and a monk—desiring to disparage him, desiring to give him a bad reputation, desiring to humiliate him—says,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc24:2.2.5"
msgid "“cīvarahetu … pe … pūjanahetu ovadatī”ti bhaṇati, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "“He instructs for the sake of robe-cloth/for the sake of almsfood/for the sake of a dwelling/for the sake of medicines/for the sake of honor/for the sake of respect/for the sake of deference/for the sake of veneration/for the sake of worship,” he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc24:2.2.6"
msgid "Anupasampannaṃ saṃghena sammataṃ vā asammataṃ vā bhikkhunovādakaṃ avaṇṇaṃ kattukāmo ayasaṃ kattukāmo maṅkukattukāmo evaṃ vadeti—"
msgstr "When someone who is not fully ordained is an instructor of nuns, whether or not he has been agreed upon by the Order as such, and a monk—desiring to disparage him, desiring to give him a bad reputation, desiring to humiliate him—says,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc24:2.2.7"
msgid "“cīvarahetu piṇḍapātahetu senāsanahetu gilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhārahetu sakkārahetu garukārahetu mānanahetu vandanahetu pūjanahetu ovadatī”ti bhaṇati, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "“He instructs for the sake of robe-cloth/for the sake of almsfood/for the sake of a dwelling/for the sake of medicines/for the sake of honor/for the sake of respect/for the sake of deference/for the sake of veneration/for the sake of worship,” he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc24:2.2.8"
msgid "Adhammakamme dhammakammasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If it is an illegitimate procedure, but he perceives it as legitimate, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc24:2.2.9"
msgid "Adhammakamme vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If it is an illegitimate procedure, but he is unsure if it is, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc24:2.2.10"
msgid "Adhammakamme adhammakammasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If it is an illegitimate procedure, and he perceives it as illegitimate, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc24:2.3.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Non-offenses"

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: sc9, pts-cs-bu-pc24.2.3, pts-vp-en.2.281, ms2V_556
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc24:2.3.1"
msgid "Anāpatti—"
msgstr "There is no offense:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc24:2.3.2"
msgid "pakatiyā cīvarahetu piṇḍapātahetu senāsanahetu gilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhārahetu sakkārahetu garukārahetu mānanahetu vandanahetu pūjanahetu ovadantaṃ bhaṇati, ummattakassa, ādikammikassāti."
msgstr "if he normally gives the instruction for the sake of robe-cloth/for the sake of almsfood/for the sake of a dwelling/for the sake of medicines/for the sake of honor/for the sake of respect/for the sake of deference/for the sake of veneration/for the sake of worship;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc24:2.3.3"
msgid "ummattakassa,"
msgstr "if he is insane;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc24:2.3.4"
msgid "ādikammikassāti."
msgstr "if he is the first offender."

#. HTML: </p><hr><p class="endsutta">
#. REF: sc10, ms2V_557
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc24:2.3.5"
msgid "Āmisasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ catutthaṃ."
msgstr "The fourth rule, the training rule on worldly gain, is finished."
